22:47.680 --> 22:49.840
Well, the lady, her eyes are streaming.

22:49.840 --> 22:50.673
Do excuse us.

22:52.870 --> 22:54.200
Ladies?

22:54.200 --> 22:55.033
Are you decent?

22:56.690 --> 22:58.050
Sorry, I've got the owner here.

22:58.050 --> 23:00.345
- [Guest] I think we've
figured out what that smell is.

23:00.345 --> 23:01.370
- [Gordon] Oh, really?

23:01.370 --> 23:03.530
- [Guest] There's all dust inside.

23:03.530 --> 23:06.190
- [Gordon] Oh, shit, there you go.

23:06.190 --> 23:07.900
- It's just, my eyes are tearing.

23:07.900 --> 23:10.427
- [Gordon] When was that cleaned last?

23:10.427 --> 23:12.410
- [Brian] That's really
a daily thing that...

23:12.410 --> 23:13.280
- [Gordon] Daily?

23:13.280 --> 23:15.610
- [Brian] Yeah, should be,
sure, yeah, absolutely.

23:15.610 --> 23:17.810
- [Gordon] That is not daily.

23:17.810 --> 23:20.990
Look at that.

23:20.990 --> 23:21.843
That's why.

23:23.480 --> 23:25.547
Jesus Christ almighty.

23:27.980 --> 23:30.688
No wonder the poor lady's broken out.

23:30.688 --> 23:34.050
- It's, like, the back of
my throat is all scratchy.

23:34.050 --> 23:36.530
- Is there an alternative room
we can use for the ladies?

23:36.530 --> 23:38.030
- I'll double-check right away.

23:38.030 --> 23:40.690
- Have a drink downstairs,
a little bite to eat,

23:40.690 --> 23:41.732
but we can sort something out.

23:41.732 --> 23:42.565
- Okay.

23:45.292 --> 23:47.875
(Gordon sighs)

23:48.935 --> 23:50.935
- [Gordon] What a night.

23:53.280 --> 23:55.320
The big problem here is
that there's no direction

23:55.320 --> 23:57.430
for the hotel, for the
restaurant, for the gazebo,

23:57.430 --> 23:59.210
not even for the car park.

23:59.210 --> 24:01.360
Ben is like a headless
chicken that's checked out,

24:01.360 --> 24:03.780
and Brian's like this scared school kid

24:03.780 --> 24:06.900
that is not qualified to
run a fucking beach bar,

24:06.900 --> 24:08.270
let alone a hotel on a beach.

24:08.270 --> 24:10.490
So...
(sighs)

24:12.209 --> 24:13.043
This is bad.

24:14.670 --> 24:15.703
This is really grim.

24:17.710 --> 24:19.330
- [James] Brian, am I wrong?

24:19.330 --> 24:21.130
I feel like we blew it tonight.

24:21.130 --> 24:24.410
- No, man, it is what it is, you know.

24:24.410 --> 24:25.260
Don't worry, man.

24:26.187 --> 24:28.687
(funky music)

24:33.455 --> 24:35.036
- [Gordon] Oh, for God's sake.

24:35.036 --> 24:38.050
(upbeat music)

24:38.050 --> 24:40.110
After a very frustrating night,

24:40.110 --> 24:42.640
I woke up this morning hopeful
that Brian would be eager

24:42.640 --> 24:44.573
to admit his faults at the Beachfront.

24:45.640 --> 24:47.060
That wasn't the case.

24:47.060 --> 24:49.000
Even after a staff meeting,

24:49.000 --> 24:51.540
none of the problems are
sinking in with Brian.

24:51.540 --> 24:53.660
So I reached out to his brother Eric

24:53.660 --> 24:55.510
who is continuing to fund the business,

24:55.510 --> 24:58.460
and I'm hoping Brian can
start to see the damage

24:58.460 --> 24:59.293
he has done.

25:00.690 --> 25:02.350
- [Eric] Hey, what's up, guys?

25:02.350 --> 25:03.643
- [Gordon] Thanks for coming in.

25:05.580 --> 25:06.980
- [Eric] Why is Ramsay here?

25:10.750 --> 25:12.560
- Your brother just asked you a question.

25:12.560 --> 25:14.080
Why did you call me here?

25:14.080 --> 25:17.377
- I've got a lot of issues
that I need to take care of.

25:17.377 --> 25:19.360
- You don't look like
a man that's in pain.

25:19.360 --> 25:20.740
You don't look like a
man that's struggling.

25:20.740 --> 25:23.130
You don't look like a
man that's lost control.

25:23.130 --> 25:26.290
You look like you're
bouncing around having fun.

25:26.290 --> 25:27.210
The business is hurting,

25:27.210 --> 25:28.183
you're hurting your brother's business,

25:28.183 --> 25:30.860
and you're not realising it.

25:30.860 --> 25:32.450
- [Eric] It does reach a ceiling

25:32.450 --> 25:34.873
where Brian, you're gonna
have to get cut off.

25:39.720 --> 25:42.310
- I'll respect it, but you got
to let me know how much time,

25:42.310 --> 25:44.350
and I'll make it.

25:44.350 --> 25:45.183
I'll make it.

25:47.340 --> 25:49.240
- Two more months, and then that's it.

25:51.120 --> 25:52.660
- Two months.

25:52.660 --> 25:53.713
- Here's my promise.

25:54.810 --> 25:56.460
I will focus so hard,

25:56.460 --> 26:00.050
and I will be able to
pay you in eight weeks.

26:00.050 --> 26:01.240
I'll pay you in eight weeks.

26:01.240 --> 26:03.150
I'll pay you in eight weeks.

26:03.150 --> 26:04.050
- [Eric] 30 grand.

26:09.081 --> 26:10.330
- You got to give me 90 days.

26:10.330 --> 26:12.080
I mean, you got to give me 90 days.

26:14.010 --> 26:15.300
- He's just given you eight weeks,

26:15.300 --> 26:17.123
you've just asked for 12 weeks.

26:18.490 --> 26:22.870
You can't continue depending
on your little brother's cash

26:22.870 --> 26:25.040
to float your dreams.

26:25.040 --> 26:26.920
- I just need you to make sure

26:26.920 --> 26:28.470
not to screw this one up again.

26:30.510 --> 26:31.910
- I'm not gonna screw it up.

26:33.250 --> 26:34.313
- I'm not convinced.

26:35.462 --> 26:36.390
No, no, no.

26:36.390 --> 26:38.340
You're lucky he's your fucking brother.

26:40.150 --> 26:42.160
- [Brian] Eric, I got you, eight months--

26:42.160 --> 26:42.993
- [Eric] Eight weeks.

26:42.993 --> 26:44.540
Eight weeks, or you're cut off.

26:44.540 --> 26:46.304
That's all there is to it, man.

26:46.304 --> 26:48.804
(Brian sighs)

26:49.755 --> 26:52.439
(thunder claps)

26:52.439 --> 26:54.710
(rain pouring)

26:54.710 --> 26:56.890
- [Gordon] How important
is your reputation to you?

26:56.890 --> 26:59.060
- [Brian] That's the most
important thing in my world.

26:59.060 --> 27:00.380
- And on a scale of 1 to 10,

27:00.380 --> 27:02.240
your reputation in this town now?

27:02.240 --> 27:04.200
- I'd give myself a good eight.

27:04.200 --> 27:05.033
- A good eight?

27:05.033 --> 27:06.730
A strong eight?
- [Brian] Absolutely.

27:07.830 --> 27:09.440
- [Gordon] So these are customers

27:09.440 --> 27:10.600
that have gone out of their way

27:10.600 --> 27:13.950
to spend their hard-earned
cash supporting your business.

27:13.950 --> 27:15.490
You must recognise a few of these faces.

27:15.490 --> 27:16.550
- [Brian] Absolutely I do.

27:16.550 --> 27:18.210
- [Gordon] Let's start off with
the lady in the blue shirt.

27:18.210 --> 27:19.123
You know her very well.

27:19.123 --> 27:21.067
- [Brian] Hey, Plythe.
- Hi, Brian.

27:21.067 --> 27:22.880
- How do you know each other?

27:22.880 --> 27:24.140
- I market Brian.

27:24.140 --> 27:25.940
- You're a spokesperson for that business?

27:25.940 --> 27:26.773
- Yes.

27:26.773 --> 27:27.627
- Can you be honest with this one?

27:27.627 --> 27:28.900
- [Plythe] Yes, I can.

27:28.900 --> 27:31.853
The service is very bad.

27:32.870 --> 27:34.410
I've brought people here.

27:34.410 --> 27:36.030
I've been up at the bar myself

27:36.030 --> 27:37.800
trying to order even just a water.

27:37.800 --> 27:39.808
That's been tough.

27:39.808 --> 27:40.870
- Do you not listen to the advice,

27:40.870 --> 27:42.313
in terms of sloppy service?

27:44.048 --> 27:45.940
- Absolutely, I listen.

27:45.940 --> 27:48.740
I do listen, I do listen, I do listen.

27:48.740 --> 27:51.260
- [Gordon] Do you offload
that to your team?

27:51.260 --> 27:52.930
- No, I don't, I don't.

27:52.930 --> 27:55.260
- So that's why it's not dealt with.

27:55.260 --> 27:56.557
Sir, your experience?

27:56.557 --> 27:58.530
- [Diner] We ordered a chicken sandwich.

27:58.530 --> 28:01.441
When the chicken sandwich
came out, it was raw.

28:01.441 --> 28:03.100
It was raw, and it was
mushy in the middle.

28:03.100 --> 28:05.110
I could've got sick from that.

28:05.110 --> 28:06.837
And I love your bar, because
I can come here late night,

28:06.837 --> 28:08.580
and I can get free drinks.

28:08.580 --> 28:10.240
Two for me and two for my
buddy, and pay for one.

28:10.240 --> 28:11.173
We got five.

28:12.220 --> 28:14.420
- Wow, unbelievable.

28:14.420 --> 28:15.253
Sir?

28:15.253 --> 28:17.290
- [Guest] My first experience
here was a Super Bowl party

28:17.290 --> 28:18.130
that you advertised

28:18.130 --> 28:20.310
and I actually had some
out-of-town guests.

28:20.310 --> 28:21.490
Food was very mediocre.

28:21.490 --> 28:23.750
The crab cakes were like sawdust.

28:23.750 --> 28:25.080
They were horrible that night.

28:25.080 --> 28:26.690
After the game was over,

28:26.690 --> 28:29.390
a couple rowdy fans
started a little brawl.

28:29.390 --> 28:31.200
We had drinks thrown on us.

28:31.200 --> 28:32.033
- [Gordon] Wow.

28:32.033 --> 28:33.280
- [Guest] The other
thing I'd like to say is

28:33.280 --> 28:34.990
if I'm staying on the ocean,

28:34.990 --> 28:36.470
I love to fall asleep with the window open

28:36.470 --> 28:38.160
and hear the ocean.

28:38.160 --> 28:38.993
You can't do that here,

28:38.993 --> 28:40.533
you hear music all night long.

28:41.500 --> 28:44.040
- I honestly stayed here myself once.

28:44.040 --> 28:47.670
I tried to call down, because
our sheets were dirty.

28:47.670 --> 28:48.610
You couldn't even call.

28:48.610 --> 28:50.260
Like, nobody answered.

28:50.260 --> 28:53.430
And literally, I think
the biggest problem for me

28:53.430 --> 28:54.540
is the mixed message.

28:54.540 --> 28:57.580
It's like, are you a bar,
or are you a restaurant?

28:57.580 --> 28:59.900
Because we're paying $150 for dinner.

28:59.900 --> 29:03.700
However, there's people
walking in in bikinis, drunk.

29:03.700 --> 29:04.533
- Damn.

29:05.630 --> 29:07.350
Listen, this feedback has been crucial.

29:07.350 --> 29:08.700
Anything you'd like to say?

29:10.220 --> 29:11.370
- [Brian] Thank you guys.

29:11.370 --> 29:12.344
You guys rock, man.

29:12.344 --> 29:13.220
- Hey, man, thanks.
- [Brian] Thank you.

29:13.220 --> 29:14.816
I'm telling you, I'll make
you proud, I promise you.

29:14.816 --> 29:15.649
- [Diner] All right.

29:15.649 --> 29:16.482
(crowd clapping)

29:16.482 --> 29:18.760
- [Gordon] Brian, let's
have a little word.

29:18.760 --> 29:19.593
Let's go.

29:20.730 --> 29:22.220
It's not a time for high-fiving.

29:22.220 --> 29:23.500
Fuck, I'm embarrassed.

29:23.500 --> 29:25.090
What the fuck are you hugging them for?

29:25.090 --> 29:26.780
- [Brian] I know that they
care, I do know they care.

29:26.780 --> 29:28.270
- [Gordon] A raw chicken sandwich?

29:28.270 --> 29:29.573
That's not an eight.

29:30.490 --> 29:31.810
That is not an 8 out of 10.

29:31.810 --> 29:33.380
Do you think they're set up?

29:33.380 --> 29:34.630
Do you think this is a TV show,

29:34.630 --> 29:36.560
and we're just gonna spout off?

29:36.560 --> 29:38.650
These people aren't exaggerating.

29:38.650 --> 29:41.033
They're real, they're real customers.

29:41.900 --> 29:44.558
You're turning into a laughingstock.

29:44.558 --> 29:45.740
- Yeah, I know, it's not good.

29:45.740 --> 29:47.400
- [Gordon] The jury is out with me.

29:47.400 --> 29:50.070
I've never come this far
and still sat on the fence

29:50.070 --> 29:51.630
in an undecided way.

29:51.630 --> 29:54.400
But fucking listen up,
and listen carefully.

29:54.400 --> 29:56.177
The partying, the free-for-all--

29:56.177 --> 29:59.280
"I'm paying for one drink,
they're giving me five,"

29:59.280 --> 30:00.733
in front of your eyes.

30:02.900 --> 30:06.770
Tomorrow you turn up here
looking like an owner.

30:06.770 --> 30:07.603
- Understood.

30:07.603 --> 30:08.960
- [Gordon] You've got a lot on your plate,

30:08.960 --> 30:12.803
but get your head out the
fucking clouds, and get real.

30:15.340 --> 30:16.173
Fuck off.

30:16.173 --> 30:17.650
- [Brian] I've got this, Gordon.

30:17.650 --> 30:18.483
I'll show you.

30:21.895 --> 30:23.553
(suspenseful music)

30:23.553 --> 30:26.386
(water splashing)

30:27.290 --> 30:28.410
- [Gordon] Even though I wasn't won over

30:28.410 --> 30:29.750
by Brian's commitment,

30:29.750 --> 30:33.460
I went ahead and designed a
new concept for the Beachfront.

30:33.460 --> 30:36.060
My team and I completely
overhauled the rooms

30:36.060 --> 30:39.720
and added a beach club to
the unused outdoor space.

30:39.720 --> 30:42.020
I'm really hoping Brian
can see the potential

30:42.020 --> 30:42.953
he has to offer.

30:44.900 --> 30:46.040
Good morning.
- Good morning.

30:46.040 --> 30:48.230
- Well, I wish it was a good morning.

30:48.230 --> 30:50.920
What did I ask you to
come in to work today?

30:50.920 --> 30:51.753
What did I say?

30:51.753 --> 30:52.660
What was the one thing I said to you?

30:52.660 --> 30:53.930
Come in as a...

30:53.930 --> 30:55.890
- Boss.
- A boss.

30:55.890 --> 30:59.943
Right now, you look like a towel boy.

31:01.040 --> 31:04.280
I mean, sunglasses round your neck,

31:04.280 --> 31:06.240
badge on there, shorts on there.

31:06.240 --> 31:07.950
Who are you?

31:07.950 --> 31:09.183
Give me the name badge.

31:16.040 --> 31:18.673
Stand out from the
crowd, you're the owner.

31:19.540 --> 31:22.730
I've had a really rough
night, and so has my team.

31:22.730 --> 31:26.090
Get out of here, get changed,
and come back like an owner.

31:26.090 --> 31:27.440
Now fuck off.

31:27.440 --> 31:28.273
- [Brian] Ready.

31:29.130 --> 31:29.993
- Honestly.

31:31.270 --> 31:32.103
- Gordon--
- [Gordon] Hurry up.

31:32.103 --> 31:34.563
No, no, no, no, no, I'm not listening.

31:36.360 --> 31:38.630
- [Brian] Gordon, I'm
coming back like a boss.

31:38.630 --> 31:41.180
I'm ready to make this whole
Fort Pierce community--

31:41.180 --> 31:42.900
Gordon--
- [Gordon] Get out of here.

31:42.900 --> 31:44.053
Seatbelt on.

31:45.170 --> 31:47.300
No doors and no seatbelt.

31:47.300 --> 31:48.133
Oh, my God.

31:51.615 --> 31:52.897
- [Brian] I'll be back.

31:52.897 --> 31:53.730
- "I'll be back."

31:53.730 --> 31:55.127
- [Brian] And I'll be ready.

32:01.001 --> 32:02.800
(bright orchestral music)

32:02.800 --> 32:05.060
(water splashing)

32:05.060 --> 32:06.807
- [Gordon] Brian returned
looking like an owner,

32:06.807 --> 32:10.050
and I'm hoping that translates
into his role as a boss.

32:10.050 --> 32:10.990
- [Gordon] Let's go.

32:10.990 --> 32:11.823
Joey, quickstep.

32:11.823 --> 32:12.656
Let's go.
- Wow.

32:12.656 --> 32:15.030
- [Gordon] It's time to
reveal to Brian and his staff

32:15.030 --> 32:17.710
the newly renovated
Beachfront Inn and Inlet.

32:17.710 --> 32:19.236
- Oh, my God.

32:19.236 --> 32:20.069
Wow!

32:20.069 --> 32:22.070
- [Liza] This is what I envisioned.

32:22.070 --> 32:23.010
Wow.

32:23.010 --> 32:23.843
- Wow, wow, wow.

32:23.843 --> 32:24.676
- [Gordon] First of all,

32:24.676 --> 32:26.960
this is not the spring break
hangout that's gone wrong,

32:26.960 --> 32:29.260
this is a proper beachfront room.

32:29.260 --> 32:30.133
- [Brian] Sweet.

32:31.800 --> 32:33.399
- Oh, yeah.

32:33.399 --> 32:34.232
Oh, yeah.

32:34.232 --> 32:35.810
- [Brian] It's the Inlet.

32:35.810 --> 32:36.840
- [Joey] It's home.
- [Brian] Oh my God.

32:36.840 --> 32:38.200
- [Joey] Whoa, the floor.

32:38.200 --> 32:40.460
- [Brian] I love it, it's perfect.

32:40.460 --> 32:41.650
- You've got a tangible asset here

32:41.650 --> 32:43.880
that can help lift this business,

32:43.880 --> 32:45.960
and more importantly, start making money.

32:45.960 --> 32:46.793
- Awesome.

32:46.793 --> 32:48.770
- Brian, you need to get
a grip of this business,

32:48.770 --> 32:51.950
and you need to realise
what's at stake here.

32:51.950 --> 32:53.230
I need to be convinced.

32:53.230 --> 32:55.410
I need to see you stepping up as a boss.

32:55.410 --> 32:57.990
Ben and Joey, we're re-launching
that restaurant tonight,

32:57.990 --> 33:00.170
so I'm gonna go through that menu.

33:00.170 --> 33:01.570
Return downstairs, get organised,

33:01.570 --> 33:03.630
and start finding your way.

33:03.630 --> 33:05.275
Let's go.

33:05.275 --> 33:06.273
- [Ben] Oh, man.

33:08.120 --> 33:10.530
- [Gordon] After observing dinner service,

33:10.530 --> 33:12.300
I saw the Beachfront kitchen wasn't set up

33:12.300 --> 33:14.290
to handle such a massive menu.

33:14.290 --> 33:16.510
So I redesigned a smaller menu

33:16.510 --> 33:18.433
that is easy for Ben to execute.

33:19.350 --> 33:20.183
Okay, guys.

33:20.183 --> 33:21.640
Small menu, let's run from the top.

33:21.640 --> 33:22.610
Appetisers.

33:22.610 --> 33:25.870
Lobster mac and cheese done
with the correct pasta, Ben.

33:25.870 --> 33:28.440
Steamed clams, again, great
sharing for the table.

33:28.440 --> 33:32.200
Wings off the smoker, so
it stays nice and crisp,

33:32.200 --> 33:33.510
and a chicken Cobb salad.

33:33.510 --> 33:36.920
Entrees, pan-seared
scallops, easy, three sears.

33:36.920 --> 33:38.670
Ahi tuna, fresh.

33:38.670 --> 33:40.360
And then, of course, the mahi-mahi.

33:40.360 --> 33:42.090
It's small, it's inviting,

33:42.090 --> 33:45.260
and tonight I've just been told

33:45.260 --> 33:47.710
that we've got the mayor in for dinner.

33:47.710 --> 33:49.280
One person we can reach out to

33:49.280 --> 33:52.910
to send the message back in
the community, "This is it."

33:52.910 --> 33:53.743
Dig in.

33:55.170 --> 33:57.030
- [Liza] That sauce is fabulous.

33:57.030 --> 33:57.863
- Oh, my god.

33:59.260 --> 34:00.783
Wow.

34:00.783 --> 34:04.520
(suspenseful orchestral music)

34:04.520 --> 34:06.610
- [Gordon] It's time to
re-launch the Beachfront.

34:06.610 --> 34:08.230
I've put a plan in place,

34:08.230 --> 34:10.639
and I'm really hoping
Brian can finally show me

34:10.639 --> 34:12.320
that he's ready to run his business.

34:12.320 --> 34:13.620
- [Brian] All right, everybody.

34:13.620 --> 34:15.020
Listen up.

34:15.020 --> 34:16.949
Tonight is a big service.

34:16.949 --> 34:19.500
There's not many opportunities like this.

34:19.500 --> 34:21.400
You have to take advantage of it.

34:21.400 --> 34:23.699
I need you guys all to
get together right now

34:23.699 --> 34:24.650
and bring it in.

34:24.650 --> 34:26.007
One, two, three.

34:26.007 --> 34:27.690
- [Everybody] go, Inlet!

34:27.690 --> 34:28.760
(staff cheering)

34:28.760 --> 34:30.510
- [Gordon] Brian, Brian.

34:30.510 --> 34:32.150
Let's just get real for a
couple of seconds, yeah?

34:32.150 --> 34:32.983
- [Brian] Yup, yes, sir.

34:32.983 --> 34:35.420
- You forgot the fucking
most important thing tonight.

34:36.380 --> 34:37.889
Who is in for dinner tonight?

34:37.889 --> 34:39.710
You haven't even told the staff.

34:39.710 --> 34:42.090
Possibly the most important
person in this town.

34:42.090 --> 34:43.407
- We have the mayor in tonight, you guys.

34:43.407 --> 34:45.070
- The mayor, and that's just not something

34:45.070 --> 34:46.730
that happens every fucking week.

34:46.730 --> 34:48.580
You have to bring it together tonight.

34:48.580 --> 34:50.400
You have to work as a team.

34:50.400 --> 34:53.199
Sort it out, guys, we're
opening in five minutes.

34:53.199 --> 34:54.699
- [Brian] Come on.

34:54.699 --> 34:59.080
(suspenseful orchestral music)

34:59.080 --> 34:59.967
- [Liza] Checking in?
- Checking in.

34:59.967 --> 35:01.230
- [Liza] All right.

35:01.230 --> 35:02.350
- [James] Welcome to the Inlet.

35:02.350 --> 35:03.580
- [Brian] Good evening, good evening.

35:03.580 --> 35:05.230
- [Guest] This is lovely.

35:05.230 --> 35:06.120
- Enjoy dinner.

35:06.120 --> 35:08.800
An amazing array of appetisers,

35:08.800 --> 35:10.580
and the entrees are to die for.

35:10.580 --> 35:11.413
- [Joey] Tortoise and the hare.

35:11.413 --> 35:13.560
Slow and steady wins the race.

35:13.560 --> 35:15.098
- [Gordon] So first ticket on, yes?

35:15.098 --> 35:17.471
- [Joey] Yeah.
- [Gordon] Good.

35:17.471 --> 35:18.310
- [Hostess] Hi, how are you?

35:18.310 --> 35:19.233
Welcome to the Inlet.

35:19.233 --> 35:20.478
Hi, guys, just the two of us today?

35:20.478 --> 35:21.347
- It's the mayor.

35:21.347 --> 35:23.257
Okay, yeah, that's the mayor.

35:23.257 --> 35:25.089
Now where are you sitting her?

35:25.089 --> 35:25.922
Come on, where?

35:25.922 --> 35:26.755
- [Brian] Well, they were gonna--

35:26.755 --> 35:27.617
- Well, give her a choice.

35:27.617 --> 35:28.940
"Would you like to sit inside or outside?"

35:28.940 --> 35:30.530
It's her choice.

35:30.530 --> 35:31.867
- Welcome, how are you?

35:31.867 --> 35:33.180
Thank you for coming in.

35:33.180 --> 35:34.491
- [Mayor] So nice to see you.
- [Brian] Thank you guys.

35:34.491 --> 35:35.324
- [Gordon] Likewise.
- [Brian] Thank you.

35:35.324 --> 35:36.480
- [Gordon] It's an absolute pleasure.

35:36.480 --> 35:39.140
I'll leave you in the hands
of our manager-owner Brian.

35:39.140 --> 35:39.980
- Follow me, guys.

35:39.980 --> 35:40.813
- Welcome.

35:40.813 --> 35:41.849
John, good to see you, sir.

35:41.849 --> 35:42.682
Likewise.

35:43.700 --> 35:44.793
- [Brian] Okay, guys.

35:47.340 --> 35:48.200
All right, mayor.

35:48.200 --> 35:49.810
Wherever you'd like inside.

35:49.810 --> 35:52.290
- [Joey] I got a chicken
burger ready at your leisure.

35:52.290 --> 35:54.190
- [Ben] Chicken burger?

35:54.190 --> 35:56.237
- Ben, has Brian told you the mayor's in?

35:56.237 --> 35:57.273
- No, he has not.

35:58.364 --> 36:00.690
- [Gordon] Unreal.

36:00.690 --> 36:04.590
Brian, your chef doesn't
even know the mayor's in.

36:04.590 --> 36:05.650
- Ah.

36:05.650 --> 36:07.420
- [Gordon] You don't
think he deserves to know?

36:07.420 --> 36:08.253
- [Brian] Yes, he does.
- [Gordon] Come on.

36:08.253 --> 36:09.086
Come on, then.

36:09.086 --> 36:10.275
- Ben?
- [Ben] Yes?

36:10.275 --> 36:11.570
- The mayor's in at table seven.

36:11.570 --> 36:13.263
- [Ben] Heard, table seven.
- [Brian] Inside.

36:14.630 --> 36:16.220
- Am I good, Ben?

36:16.220 --> 36:18.897
I've got that blackened chicken for you.

36:18.897 --> 36:20.048
And that's it.

36:20.048 --> 36:20.881
- Thanks for your fucking help.

36:20.881 --> 36:22.110
- [Joey] Ben, you need to be the captain,

36:22.110 --> 36:25.130
and right now I'm not convinced.

36:25.130 --> 36:28.000
Let's get serious about
this business and do this.

36:28.000 --> 36:29.852
- Is the mayor's order in?

36:29.852 --> 36:31.096
Have they sent their appetisers yet?

36:31.096 --> 36:32.123
- [Kelly] Yes, it is.

36:32.123 --> 36:33.220
- Have they hit the table?

36:33.220 --> 36:34.610
- [Kelly] No, I put their food in.

36:34.610 --> 36:36.550
He wanted the salad
and the fried calamari,

36:36.550 --> 36:37.810
and she wanted the mahi.

36:37.810 --> 36:39.190
- Mahi, okay, great.

36:39.190 --> 36:40.610
So again, check it, that's
your hot ticket tonight.

36:40.610 --> 36:43.628
Do you know what's happening
in your kitchen at the moment?

36:43.628 --> 36:44.461
No, look at me.

36:44.461 --> 36:45.471
Do you know what's happening in there?

36:45.471 --> 36:46.304
You haven't got a fucking clue.

36:46.304 --> 36:48.550
You have to get into the kitchen,

36:48.550 --> 36:49.550
find out what's going on.

36:49.550 --> 36:50.383
Let's go.

36:52.570 --> 36:53.770
- [Ben] Look behind you.

36:55.190 --> 36:57.292
Ow, I burned my forehead.

36:57.292 --> 36:58.925
- Oh, man.
- Excuse me.

36:58.925 --> 36:59.758
- [Diner] I'm starving.

36:59.758 --> 37:00.943
- So, What did you guys order?

37:01.920 --> 37:05.863
- I got the mahi-mahi and a
salad, and he got an appetiser.

37:06.770 --> 37:08.560
- The mayor is the only person sat

37:08.560 --> 37:10.010
with nothing in front of her.

37:10.949 --> 37:14.270
- [Brian] Yeah.
- [Gordon] Please?

37:14.270 --> 37:15.773
- [Ben] All right, two tunas.

37:15.773 --> 37:18.440
- Can I have table 15's appetisers ASAP?

37:18.440 --> 37:19.590
It's the mayor.

37:19.590 --> 37:20.930
- [Ben] 15?
- 15.

37:20.930 --> 37:22.810
- [Ben] I was told seven.
- [Gordon] Fucking hell.

37:22.810 --> 37:23.980
- Sorry, miscommunication.

37:23.980 --> 37:25.210
- They're sat on 15, right?

37:25.210 --> 37:26.218
- I made a mistake, it's 15.

37:26.218 --> 37:27.250
- Okay, I need two house salads right now,

37:27.250 --> 37:28.090
before anything else.

37:28.090 --> 37:29.820
Right this second.

37:29.820 --> 37:32.263
- [Joey] Brian didn't know
what table the mayor was at.

37:33.430 --> 37:35.750
It seems like the biggest
thing Brian changed

37:35.750 --> 37:37.070
was his wardrobe.

37:37.070 --> 37:38.100
- Two house are in the window.

37:38.100 --> 37:39.490
Two house need to go, 15.

37:39.490 --> 37:40.540
- Have you seen the salads?

37:40.540 --> 37:41.440
- [Ben] No.

37:41.440 --> 37:42.306
- [Gordon] Ben.
- Yes, sir?

37:42.306 --> 37:43.139
- You need to see that.

37:43.139 --> 37:45.387
You need to taste that and see
everything he's doing there.

37:45.387 --> 37:47.590
- [Ben] Terry, it's
too much dressing, bro.

37:47.590 --> 37:48.423
Redo it.

37:48.423 --> 37:49.256
- His salad's overdressed.

37:49.256 --> 37:51.190
It's soggy as shit, wrong dressing.

37:51.190 --> 37:52.710
Ben?
- [Ben] Yes, sir?

37:52.710 --> 37:54.260
- What I need to hear is a bit of a voice.

37:54.260 --> 37:55.923
If we go silent, we'll go down.

37:56.916 --> 37:59.590
(suspenseful music)

37:59.590 --> 38:01.600
For tonight's re-launch
of the Beachfront...

38:01.600 --> 38:02.550
Salad's overdressed.

38:02.550 --> 38:04.720
Soggy as shit, wrong dressing.

38:04.720 --> 38:07.460
I was really hoping Brian
would step up as an owner,

38:07.460 --> 38:10.360
given that I'd put everything
in place for him to succeed.

38:11.220 --> 38:12.110
- God damn it, dude.

38:12.110 --> 38:14.440
- [Gordon] But his lack of
focus has me really worried

38:14.440 --> 38:16.520
that he's not fit to run this place.

38:16.520 --> 38:17.353
Come on, Brian.

38:17.353 --> 38:18.186
- Chef Ben?

38:19.742 --> 38:20.575
- [Gordon] Come here.

38:20.575 --> 38:22.090
Come here, let's go.

38:22.090 --> 38:23.523
Your chef has shut down.

38:24.720 --> 38:25.553
- [Brian] I didn't realise it.

38:25.553 --> 38:26.386
- You didn't realise,

38:26.386 --> 38:27.780
so the first two salads for the mayor

38:27.780 --> 38:29.700
had the wrong dressing
on and were overdressed.

38:29.700 --> 38:31.560
I said, "Have you tasted
them?" he said, "No."

38:31.560 --> 38:33.010
So he hasn't got your back.

38:33.010 --> 38:34.270
When's that penny gonna drop

38:34.270 --> 38:35.970
that you're gonna turn the corner?

38:37.570 --> 38:38.480
- We'll watch Ben.

38:38.480 --> 38:41.430
If he doesn't come out of it,
we'll switch him and Joey.

38:41.430 --> 38:42.263
- Will you?

38:46.550 --> 38:49.500
- How many guacamoles
you guys got out there?

38:49.500 --> 38:51.560
Okay.
- [Staff Member] Eight.

38:51.560 --> 38:53.970
Chicken, 30 seconds.

38:53.970 --> 38:56.550
- Give me a time on the
mayor's table please, Ben.

38:56.550 --> 38:57.520
- [Ben] Table 15?

38:57.520 --> 38:58.550
- Yeah, the mayor's table.

38:58.550 --> 39:01.030
- We sold it, calamari and a mahi.

39:01.030 --> 39:02.170
- Did you see it before it went?

39:02.170 --> 39:04.740
- [Ben] I sure did, I plated everything.

39:04.740 --> 39:08.387
- The mayor hasn't got the fucking food.

39:08.387 --> 39:10.550
Brian, Brian, urgently, come here.

39:12.550 --> 39:15.352
So Ben's told me the fucking
mayor's got their food.

39:15.352 --> 39:16.185
- [Brian] Right.

39:16.185 --> 39:18.370
- And look at the mayor's table.

39:18.370 --> 39:19.203
There's nothing on there.

39:19.203 --> 39:20.510
Now look at me, look now.

39:20.510 --> 39:22.256
Hey, we're about to go down here.

39:22.256 --> 39:23.820
And I'm gonna get in my fucking car,

39:23.820 --> 39:24.850
and I'm gonna get the fuck out of here

39:24.850 --> 39:26.430
if you don't get a grip,

39:26.430 --> 39:28.110
'cause this is a fucking joke.

39:28.110 --> 39:31.050
Now you better get in there and
tell your executive chef Ben

39:31.050 --> 39:33.080
that the mayor hasn't got their food

39:33.080 --> 39:34.780
and find out where the fuck it is.

39:37.830 --> 39:39.560
- Ben, the mayor has not gotten her food.

39:39.560 --> 39:41.160
- I put it in the window.

39:41.160 --> 39:41.993
- [Brian] Where is the Mayor's food?

39:41.993 --> 39:43.663
- I'll make it right now,
I'll make it right now.

39:45.760 --> 39:47.730
- [Mayor] Be nice to have
some food right about now.

39:47.730 --> 39:49.050
- [Ben] Let's try the mayor's food again.

39:49.050 --> 39:50.390
- [Gina] Terry, I need a Caesar right now.

39:50.390 --> 39:52.180
- [Terry] It's coming right now, Gina.

39:52.180 --> 39:53.013
- Order up.

39:54.950 --> 39:55.783
- [Gordon] Where's that going?

39:55.783 --> 39:56.829
- [Gina] 51.

39:56.829 --> 39:58.163
- 51, come here, you.

40:01.640 --> 40:02.827
What is that?

40:02.827 --> 40:03.942
- [Brian] Undercooked.

40:03.942 --> 40:06.410
- That is undercooked?

40:06.410 --> 40:08.074
Young lady, come here.

40:08.074 --> 40:09.977
What does that chicken look like to you?

40:11.522 --> 40:14.000
- It looks blackened and dry.

40:14.000 --> 40:14.833
- [Gordon] Thank you.

40:14.833 --> 40:15.713
So it's dry.

40:17.570 --> 40:19.970
Young lady, how would you
describe that chicken?

40:21.220 --> 40:22.380
- It looks kind of dry.

40:22.380 --> 40:23.250
- Very dry.
- [Server] Very dry.

40:23.250 --> 40:24.877
- Now you're not even a chef, are you?

40:24.877 --> 40:26.190
- [Server] No, never cooked.
- No, no.

40:26.190 --> 40:27.411
How old are you?
- [Server] I'm 20.

40:27.411 --> 40:28.510
- 20, thanks, darling.

40:28.510 --> 40:30.980
So for a 20-year-old
server who's never cooked,

40:30.980 --> 40:35.478
even she spotted it's dry,
and you're saying it's raw.

40:35.478 --> 40:38.100
Let me tell you something,
and listen carefully.

40:38.100 --> 40:39.270
I'm going.

40:39.270 --> 40:41.880
I'm packing my bags, 'cause
that is the worst thing

40:41.880 --> 40:43.060
you've said all week.

40:43.060 --> 40:46.140
It's overcooked, and
it's dry, and then you,

40:46.140 --> 40:47.503
you tell me it's raw.

40:48.628 --> 40:49.545
Good night.

40:52.987 --> 40:53.820
I'm done.

41:09.044 --> 41:13.010
(sighs) That is unreal.

41:13.010 --> 41:14.870
I mean, I am so pissed off.

41:14.870 --> 41:19.290
I can't give that guy any more advice.

41:19.290 --> 41:22.763
I can't continue to tell him
to step up and make decisions.

41:23.660 --> 41:27.290
He has a chef in there
that's just riding him

41:27.290 --> 41:28.750
and riding the business.

41:28.750 --> 41:30.490
And when you're weak,

41:30.490 --> 41:32.820
you've got no chance
of running a business.

41:32.820 --> 41:34.593
And what a shame.

41:36.530 --> 41:38.499
Un-fucking-real.

41:38.499 --> 41:41.499
(suspenseful music)

41:44.690 --> 41:46.663
- [Joey] Hot, coming around.

41:46.663 --> 41:49.663
(suspenseful music)

41:52.029 --> 41:54.790
(upbeat music)

41:54.790 --> 41:56.460
- [Gordon] I never like
to leave a business,

41:56.460 --> 41:58.600
but Brian simply wasn't listening.

41:58.600 --> 42:01.060
He missed the deadline
paying his brother back,

42:01.060 --> 42:02.800
and while it's been a slow process,

42:02.800 --> 42:05.810
my advice finally started to sink in.

42:05.810 --> 42:08.170
Four months after I
left, he made a decision

42:08.170 --> 42:12.240
to let Chef Ben go and hired
a brand new kitchen staff.

42:12.240 --> 42:15.490
On the hotel side, Brian has
made the guests a priority,

42:15.490 --> 42:18.080
giving the curfew to the
nighttime entertainment.

42:18.080 --> 42:21.030
Hopefully now with Brian
stepping up like a boss,

42:21.030 --> 42:23.723
he can lead the Beachfront
Inn the right direction.

42:56.852 --> 42:58.800
One Potato Two Potato.
